The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business
 Saturday, February 14, 2004 				 Sony slashes prices by 16%
 OUR CORRESPONDENT																								Mumbai, Feb. 13: Sony India today slashed the prices of specific products by 5 to 16 per cent to pass over the benefits of the recent customs duty reduction to its customers. 																								The price reduction in MRP will be 5-10 per cent for Wega flat colour televisions, 8-10 per cent for hi-fi systems and 8-16 per cent for camcorders and digital still cameras. 																								Our new pricing strategy will make our products available to a larger consumer base in India, head sales (CAV division) Mohit Parasher said. 																								An entry-level Wega TV will now be available at Rs 12,990. 
